race.comment: Tough dash with so many of these possessing early speed. LOKEN (6) is a lightly raced mare resuming in lesser company and worth noting did win only try course and distance. Drawn to stalk if doesn't take the front and expected to go close. BETTA BEING SINGLE (3) is from the hot Munce yard and also will find this easier. Has a tricky gate to overcome but more than enough ability for this line-up. AYE EYE BOOM (4) has been racing on the country circuit and at very least is in winning form, scoring last time at Bell. Speed mare who will take catching again here. KENTUCKY ROSE (5) was placed this course and distance two back before disappointing last time. Bold showing expected. JAIN (2) has a great record this short dash and always has to be included.
